<b>Setting up the ODBC</b><i>(some material borrowed from my professor's notes ,Dr. Delin Tan)</i>

In Windows 9x/NT, ODBC manager is in control panel, but in Windows 2000/XP, the ODBC manager is inside a folder named "Adminstrative Tools", which is a subfolder of Control Panel
\par\ql\{bml ODBC1.bmp\}\par\ql

First Click "System DSN" and then click "Add"
\par\ql\{bml ODBC2.bmp\}\par\ql

Click "Microsoft Access Driver" and then click "Finish"
\par\ql\{bml ODBC.bmp\}\par\ql

For "Data Source Name" type in <b><i>Robotech</i></b> and click "Select" to select the database from the hard drive. <i>Please note the database name is "Robotech.mdb" and is located in the program's directory</i>
\par\ql\{bml ODBC3.bmp\}\par\ql

Look for the physical address of database and click OK. Then click OK again
\par\ql\{bml ODBCaddress.bmp\}\par\ql

Finally the Robotech DSN is registered
\par\ql\{bml ODBCfinish.bmp\}\par\ql

